main event: A witness saw six or seven greenish-blue lights in formation that were visible for approximately three to four seconds.
interesting points: The witness described the lights as similar to the description in a previous questionnaire about UFOs.
The witness stated the lights traveled at a tremendous speed and were not any known type of aircraft.
The witness reported seeing the lights while observing a lunar eclipse, indicating an unusual sighting.
The witness was interested in hearing from the investigators about this sighting.
The report mentions a previous sighting on March 3, 1968, which was determined to be the reentry of a Russian ZOND satellite.
